MARnq1WoY-FY88ucIxYmGg
Rarely do I leave a place and pen immediately.  However, Leticia deserves it and then some.  Hands down best mani pedi I can remember.  She's super chill...not a barrage of questioning.  Inspects and shapes to perfection.   Salon opens at 10:00, and the online booking system wouldn't let me do a manicure and pedicure because it was 10 minutes too long given the other appointments on the books.  I showed at 9:40, and much of the staff was there already setting up.  They took me early and gave me the add on manicure that I wanted.  Having been a lady that contracted (and conquered!) a nail fungus from a reputable, but thank GOD, now defunct spa several years ago, I am militant about who and where I get my nails done.  Nail funguses are easily spread - but it's not gonna happen here!  They take every precaution for sanitization: lined buckets for the pedicures, sterilized and wrapped implements, and they even cut their buffers into individually sized 1" squares to avoid any cross contamination.    The vibe of the salon is really great.  Downtempo, chillax if you will.  I do wish the esthetician and the nail tech also took pride in their hair so that they could be a cross referral system to the stylists in the salon.    Not that this affects the service I received, but one of the stylists came to work totally unprepared.  She had to borrow gloves from Leticia and a foiling comb from another hairdresser to do her first client.  They were a kind and supportive team, but I can tell they rent because everyone has different branded items they were using...thus making the sacrifice from them beyond gracious.   Thanks for an AWESOME morning.  Loved my service and can't wait to come back on business.

